metadata.description: In “ACTOR”, I touch on my childhood trauma and lifelong effort to recover from it all. I wanted to make this one super bass-heavy to represent how fed I felt when I wrote it. This one goes out to the actor who never gave him a chance to live.

lyrics.text:
You didn’t love me for a second
For a second yeah I know
You didn’t want me talking back
You wanted me to be alone
You didn’t want me for a minute
I’m a burden I suppose
But you caught me on the ropes
Do you remember what I spoke
To you about
You held me down I was a kid
You cut me down
You never taught me how to live
You bled me out
What was all of this about
You held me down
And I can’t help but hear the sound

Fuck you
You were never around
You didn’t want me
When I was down
Actor why you love me now
Because we all play my music loud
Fuck you
You were never around
You didn’t want me
When I was down
Actor why you love me now
Because we all play my music loud

Dose me up on medicine
Keep me in the mania
Locked me in the basement
I was torn apart so you would grind me up and waste me
Could’ve been a memory but you didn’t erase me
I just wanna live
Be alright
Feel alive
But the index in my mind
Finds a line to call you back to my life
Why can’t I
Fade the memory of the things you did in time
So that I can go to sleep again at night

Fuck you
You were never around
You didn’t want me
When I was down
Actor why you love me now
Because we all play my music loud
Fuck you
You were never around
You didn’t want me
When I was down
Actor why you love me now
Because we all play my music loud
